main event: A ground-visual observation of a UFO was reported on 23 September 1950 in Freeport, Michigan. The object was seen in the morning around sunrise and remained in observation until 0745.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes from 0730 to 0745.
The observer had sighted a similar object before.
The object was described as transitioning from silver to red to yellow.
The observer used 10-power field glasses to view the object.
The document mentions a friend of the observer who also saw the object and computed that it was over the Pacific Ocean.
result: Doubtful, with possible explanations listed as 'D Probably Balloon' or 'D Probably Aircraft' due to insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: One object transitioning from silver to red to yellow
witnesses: The observer and a friend of the observer
photographs: No photographs included in the report
